.TH GAT-PATH 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-path \- print only the path to a worktree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat path
.I <ticket|^|@>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Resolves a worktree the same way
.BR gat\-go (1)
does, but always prints just the path to standard output and never changes
directory. Useful in scripts and command substitution.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-prefix " prefix"
Prefix for numeric ticket targets.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-prefix
Do not prefix a numeric target.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat path 12345
cd "$(gat path 12345)"
code "$(gat path ^)"
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-go (1)
